  "text": "The fact that hippocampal mGluR-dependent LTD is intact when PirB is removed from pyramidal cells argues that most if not all other postsynaptic and presynaptic components of eCB signaling are functional and independent of PirB. Whether endocannabinoid synthesis and release at CA3 to CA1 synapses is triggered by Group I mGluRs, voltage-gated calcium channels or NMDARs [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] , once released, eCBs bind to the endocannabinoid specific receptor, CB1R, located presynaptically [CITATION_5] .",
